#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:1
msgid "RoPA Records"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:3
msgid ""
"This guide walks through creating a complete RoPA record for a deployed "
"process bundle — from opening the editor to activating the record for public "
"publication."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:7
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:9
msgid ""
"A process bundle must already exist in the BPMN Modeler with at least one "
"linked form (so the **Hydrate from forms** button has something to read)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:10
msgid ""
"The LDE backend must be connected to PostgreSQL — the RoPA feature requires "
"database access."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:14
msgid "Step 1 — Open the RoPA Records view"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:16
msgid ""
"Click the **ScrollText** icon (🗒) in the left sidebar. If no records exist "
"yet the right panel shows an empty state. Click the **+** button in the "
"panel header to create a new record."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:20
msgid "Step 2 — Fill in the Record tab"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:22
msgid "Start with the two identifier fields at the top:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:24
msgid ""
"**Title** — a clear, human-readable name for the processing activity, e.g. "
"*Tree Felling Permit — material law assessment*."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:25
msgid ""
"**BPMN process ID** — copy the exact `id` attribute from the `<bpmn:process>"
"` element, e.g. `TreeFellingPermitSubProcess`. This is the value shown on "
"the process card in the BPMN Modeler."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:26
msgid ""
"**Process level** — select `Shell` if this record covers the AWB procedural "
"shell, or `Subprocess` if it covers a product-specific subprocess."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:28
msgid ""
"Then complete all GDPR Art. 30 mandatory fields: controller name and "
"contact, purpose, GDPR article, data subjects, recipients, retention period, "
"and security measures."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:30
msgid "Looking up the legal basis"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:32
msgid ""
"Click **Lookup from knowledge graph** next to the Legal basis field. The LDE "
"queries the RONL TriplyDB endpoint and returns a list of `eli:LegalResource` "
"entries linked to public services. Click the correct entry — both the URI "
"and label fields are populated automatically."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:34
msgid ""
"If the service is not yet registered in the knowledge graph, type the label "
"and URI manually."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:38
msgid "Step 3 — Hydrate personal data fields"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:40
msgid ""
"Switch to the **Personal Data Fields** tab. Click **Hydrate from forms**."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:42
msgid ""
"The LDE reads the BPMN XML for the process ID you entered on the Record tab, "
"extracts all `camunda:formRef` values, loads those form schemas, and creates "
"one table row per field that has a `key` property. Fields without a `key` "
"(headings, text blocks, submit buttons) are skipped automatically."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:44
msgid "For each row:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:46
msgid ""
"Confirm the **Label** — it is pre-filled from the form schema but can be "
"edited."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:47
msgid "Set the **Category** dropdown to the most appropriate data category."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:48
msgid ""
"Tick **Art. 9/10** for any field that collects health data (Art. 9 GDPR) or "
"criminal data (Art. 10 GDPR). The zorgtoeslag form fields "
"`statusZorgverzekerd` (health insurance status) and `gedetineerd` (detained) "
"are examples."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:50
msgid ""
"Remove any rows that represent routing variables or computed outputs that do "
"not constitute personal data by clicking the × on that row."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:54
msgid "Step 4 — Save the record"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:56
msgid ""
"Click **Save** in the top bar. The record is persisted to PostgreSQL and "
"appears in the left panel list with a **DRAFT** badge. The record now has a "
"UUID which is needed for the next step."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:60
msgid "Step 5 — Link to the BPMN process"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:62
msgid ""
"Switch to the **BPMN Link** tab. You will see the BPMN process ID, the "
"record's UUID, and the current value of `ronl:ropaRef` in the process XML."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:64
msgid ""
"Click **Write ronl:ropaRef to BPMN**. The UUID is injected into the BPMN XML "
"and the status indicator changes to green with a **✓ Linked** label."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:66
msgid ""
"!!! tip You can also link the record from the BPMN Modeler directly — open "
"the process there and use the **RoPA Record** dropdown panel at the bottom "
"of the process list. Both methods produce the same result."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:71
msgid "Step 6 — Activate the record"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:73
msgid ""
"Switch to the **Status** tab. The current status is **Draft**. Click **Set "
"Active**. Confirm the dialog — *\"Activating this record will make it "
"publicly visible. Continue?\"*"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:75
msgid ""
"Click **Save** again. The badge in the left panel changes to **ACTIVE** and "
"the record is now returned by `GET /v1/ropa/public` and visible on the "
"public site."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:79
msgid "Editing an existing record"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:81
msgid ""
"Click any record in the left panel to open it. Edit the fields as needed and "
"click **Save**. Changes to personal data fields (adding, removing, "
"reclassifying) take effect immediately after saving."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:83
msgid ""
"!!! note Changing the **BPMN process ID** on an existing record does not "
"automatically update the `ronl:ropaRef` in the old process XML. If you "
"change the process ID, go to the BPMN Link tab and write the link again."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:88
msgid "Archiving a record"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cropa-records.md:90
msgid ""
"When a process bundle is retired, switch the record to **Archived** on the "
"Status tab and save. Archived records are removed from the public site but "
"remain in the database for audit purposes."
msgstr ""

